<h2 class="Subheading">Test data<br /></h2>
<p>We've created a standardised open-XLSX<strong> </strong>spreadsheet to configure the LIMS with setup data of the user's choice. We populated this   instance with data of
 uniform   nature for most setup items, e.g. analysis specifications,
QC, uncertainties, turn-around time, precision, price   etc. See <a class="internal-link" href="setup-data-in-this-installation">Setup data used to configure this installation</a></p>
<p><a class="internal-link" href="setup-data-in-this-installation"><br /></a></p>
<p align="left" style="text-align: center;"><strong><img class="image-inline" src="flow-diagram-350-x" alt="Flow diagram 350 x" /><br /></strong></p>
<h3><a class="external-link" href="knowledge-centre/manual/bika-3-user-manual">User Manual </a></h3>
<p>Under construction and describing new topics at first. LIMS 2 principles still apply, if you are new to Bika, also consult the <a class="external-link" href="http://www.bikalabs.com/helpcentre/manual/bikalims20">Inkosi Bika LIMS 2 manual</a></p>
<h3>Under construction</h3>
<ul><li>Barcoding (70%)<br /></li><li>Reports (60%)</li><li>SQL (ContentMirror) (40%)<br /></li><li>User manual (20%)</li></ul>
